1
00:00:04,034 --> 00:00:06,926
Wandering a length and breadth 
of the Universe

2
00:00:07,016 --> 00:00:10,731
from lower … evolving from lower 
life forms to higher life forms

3
00:00:10,731 --> 00:00:15,919
the gradual development,
the subjective evolution of consciousness

4
00:00:16,084 --> 00:00:19,484
such a person comes 
to the human form of life.

5
00:00:19,524 --> 00:00:23,041
[Miser | Wiser]

6
00:00:23,698 --> 00:00:27,185
Upanishads are making comparative 
difference between …

7
00:00:27,468 --> 00:00:30,668
distinction between brahmans

8
00:00:31,358 --> 00:00:35,061
and the opposite of a brahman 
is what’s called a kripana,

9
00:00:35,061 --> 00:00:36,554
which means ‘miser’.

10
00:00:36,554 --> 00:00:45,098
Like we say, kripa means ‘mercy’, 
kripa-na—‘merciless’, ‘miser’.

11
00:00:45,098 --> 00:00:48,653
So what is the example given—
that as a …

12
00:00:48,993 --> 00:00:53,725
Miser accumulates 
immense wealth,

13
00:00:53,725 --> 00:00:57,557
but what is their fault—
they don’t spend it.

14
00:00:57,557 --> 00:01:00,580
They hoard the money.
So, we’re told,

15
00:01:00,580 --> 00:01:06,463
someone, a soul who evolves 
to the position of a human being,

16
00:01:06,463 --> 00:01:12,897
labdhvā su-durlabham 
idaṁ bahu-sambhavānte—
[SB: 11.9.29]

17
00:01:13,064 --> 00:01:15,936
it’s a rare opportunity,

18
00:01:15,936 --> 00:01:20,006
even biologically speaking—
to take human birth.

19
00:01:20,006 --> 00:01:23,108
So you have this great wealth

20
00:01:23,108 --> 00:01:26,408
of oppotunity
afforded by human life—

21
00:01:26,408 --> 00:01:30,436
athāto brahma jijñāsā—
for spiritual inquiry.

22
00:01:30,744 --> 00:01:33,411
But you don’t spend it on that—

23
00:01:33,411 --> 00:01:38,561
such a person is a kripana, 
a miser.

24
00:01:38,561 --> 00:01:43,149
Whereas a brahman is someone, 
who’s by the very nature

25
00:01:43,149 --> 00:01:46,115
inclined towards inner culture,

26
00:01:46,115 --> 00:01:49,115
spiritual culture, 
spiritual development.

27
00:01:49,115 --> 00:01:52,120
What others have a hard time 
getting their head around,

28
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:56,385
brahmans understand 
intuitively.

29
00:01:56,385 --> 00:02:02,295
They more easily 
can recognise the underlayer,

30
00:02:02,295 --> 00:02:05,414
beneath superficial life 
and circumstances

31
00:02:05,414 --> 00:02:07,734
the spiritual undercurrent.

32
00:02:07,734 --> 00:02:11,614
namo brahmaṇya-devāya 
go-brāhmaṇa-hitāya ca

33
00:02:11,614 --> 00:02:15,194
jagad-dhitāya kṛṣṇāya 
govindāya namo namaḥ
[Vp: 1.19.65]

34
00:02:15,194 --> 00:02:19,726
As Kṛṣṇa, we’re told, 
is affectionate for the cows,

35
00:02:19,726 --> 00:02:22,466
He also likes brahmans

36
00:02:22,466 --> 00:02:26,874
because of their natural 
spiritual inclinations.

37
00:02:26,874 --> 00:02:29,804
But again, we say, “Oh, yeah, 
they are like that, and we are not.”

38
00:02:29,804 --> 00:02:34,443
Yeah, but that’s a soul 
who’s evolved to that position.

39
00:02:34,453 --> 00:02:39,656
Our position is non-brahminical.

40
00:02:39,656 --> 00:02:42,779
Kalau śūdra-sambhavaḥ—

41
00:02:42,779 --> 00:02:51,829
even the brahmans in kali-yuga 
are spiritually deficient.

42
00:02:51,829 --> 00:02:54,136
Right, so ...

43
00:02:55,456 --> 00:02:58,315
And this is janmanā jāyate śūdraḥ—
[Mahabharata: 12.188]

44
00:02:58,315 --> 00:03:01,564
by birth everyone starts off 
in a lower position

45
00:03:01,564 --> 00:03:04,155
and acquires, can acquire

46
00:03:04,155 --> 00:03:10,245
through superior association 
and service some …

47
00:03:10,245 --> 00:03:14,026
unfold, gradual unfolding 
and development

48
00:03:14,026 --> 00:03:17,026
of virtue. Virtuous qualities.

49
00:03:17,026 --> 00:03:21,032
‘sādhu-saṅga’, ‘sādhu-saṅga’—
sarva-śāstre kaya

50
00:03:21,032 --> 00:03:26,932
lava-mātra sādhu-saṅge 
sarva-siddhi haya
[Cc: 2.22.54]

51
00:03:26,932 --> 00:03:35,624
It’s imperative to use the human life
in spiritual culture

52
00:03:35,624 --> 00:03:45,878
and that by getting
sādhu-saṅga, spiritual association.

